# .trivyignore
# Accepted / reviewed CVEs that are explicitly ignored in scans.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line, with a comment explaining WHY it is accepted.
# Every entry here must be reviewed and approved (treat like a security exception).
# Re-evaluate entries at each dependency upgrade.
#
# Example (uncomment to use):
# CVE-2023-XXXXX   # accepted: no fix available, mitigated by network isolation
# CVE-2024-XXXXX   # accepted: only affects feature not used in this image
